DURBAN – Three people were left with injuries ranging from minor to moderate after two cars collided with a stationary vehicle on the N2 northbound near Kingsway, last night. Emer-G-Med Paramedics spokesperson Kyle van Reenen said paramedics arrived on the scene just after 10.30pm. Van Reenen said one of the vehicles had overturned and was lying across the road. He said a third vehicle which was stationary at the time of the collision, burst into flames. “The injured were treated and stabilised on the scene before being taken to a nearby hospital,” said van Reenen.   In another accident, three teenagers sustained moderate injuries after the vehicle they were travelling in crashed into a lamppost on the corner of Anton Lembede Street (Smith Street) and Samore Machel Street (Aliwal Street) in the Durban’s CBD last night. Van Reenen said the driver was unharmed. Van Reenen said the teens were stabilised on the scene before being taken to hospital.   Meanwhile, one person injured following a collision on the M7 near the N2 bridge, this morning.  “He was treated and stabilised before being taken to a nearby hospital,” he said.   THE MERCURY